ployed. By rethinking the role of ideas and morality in policy changes, this book illustrates how the moral economy of activation leads to a permanent behaviourist testing of the unemployed in public debate as well as in local jobcentres.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aChung, Heejung, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaasch, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKühner, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311119668840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447349976423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447349976/original  a978-3-11-119668-8  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles